## ðŸ“Œ Math Functions Explained

* **`Math.round(x)`** - Rounds x to the nearest integer.
* **`Math.ceil(x)`** - Rounds x up to the next integer.
* **`Math.floor(x)`** - Rounds x down to the previous integer.
* **`Math.trunc(x)`** - Removes the decimal part of x.
* **`Math.pow(base, exp)`** - Returns base raised to the power of exp.
* **`Math.sqrt(x)`** - Returns the square root of x.
* **`Math.cbrt(x)`** - Returns the cube root of x.
* **`Math.abs(x)`** - Returns the absolute value of x.
* **`Math.max(x, y, ...)`** - Returns the highest value.
* **`Math.min(x, y, ...)`** - Returns the lowest value.
* **`Math.random()`** - Returns a random decimal between 0 and 1.
* **`number.toFixed(digits)`** - Converts a number to a string with specified decimals.

